            <fr:anchor>24718</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-018A</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-018A.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="All regular languages are automatical">All <fr:link href="jms-017Y.xml" title="Regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular languages</fr:link> are <fr:link href="jms-0185.xml" title="Automatical language" addr="jms-0185" type="local">automatical</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Corollary</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>If a <fr:link href="jms-016M.xml" title="Formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">language</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-017Y.xml" title="Regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular</fr:link>, then it is <fr:link href="jms-0185.xml" title="Automatical language" addr="jms-0185" type="local">automatical</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7374</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6109</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6109.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> be the set of all <fr:link href="jms-0179.xml" title="Regular expressions (abstract syntax)" addr="jms-0179" type="local">regular expressions</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> over a fixed <fr:link href="jms-016H.xml" title="Alphabet" addr="jms-016H" type="local">alphabet</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-0185.xml" title="Automatical language" addr="jms-0185" type="local">automatical</fr:link>. We wish to show that the set of all <fr:link href="jms-0179.xml" title="Regular expressions (abstract syntax)" addr="jms-0179" type="local">regular expressions</fr:link> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex> is contained in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex>. By <fr:link href="jms-0171.xml" title="Rule induction" addr="jms-0171" type="local">rule induction</fr:link> it suffices to check the following cases:</fr:p>

 <fr:ol><fr:li>We need to know that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\texttt {Sym}_{a},\texttt {Null}, \texttt {Never} \in  U]]></fr:tex>, which is the same as to say that the languages <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \{a\right \}\mathclose {}}, {\mathopen {}\left \{\epsilon \right \}\mathclose {}}, \varnothing ]]></fr:tex> are all <fr:link href="jms-0185.xml" title="Automatical language" addr="jms-0185" type="local">automatical</fr:link>. This is <fr:link href="jms-0186.xml" title="Automaticality of basic regular languages" addr="jms-0186" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-0186" /></fr:link>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>We need to show that if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R,S\in  U]]></fr:tex> then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\texttt {Union}{\mathopen {}\left (R,S\right )\mathclose {}}\in  U]]></fr:tex>, which is to say that the language <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}\cup \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (S\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-0185.xml" title="Automatical language" addr="jms-0185" type="local">automatical</fr:link> assuming that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (S\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> are. This is <fr:link href="jms-0187.xml" title="Closure of automaticality under union" addr="jms-0187" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-0187" /></fr:link>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>We need to show that if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R,S\in  U]]></fr:tex> then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\texttt {Concat}{\mathopen {}\left (R,S\right )\mathclose {}}\in  U]]></fr:tex>, which is to say that the language <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (S\right )\mathclose {}} = {\mathopen {}\left \{uv\,\middle \vert \,u\in \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}},v\in \mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (S\right )\mathclose {}}\right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-0185.xml" title="Automatical language" addr="jms-0185" type="local">automatical</fr:link> assuming that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (S\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> are. This is <fr:link href="jms-0188.xml" title="Closure of automaticality under concatenation" addr="jms-0188" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-0188" /></fr:link>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>We need to show that if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\in  U]]></fr:tex> then so is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\texttt {Star}{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}\in  U]]></fr:tex>, which is to say that if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-0185.xml" title="Automatical language" addr="jms-0185" type="local">automatical</fr:link> then so is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}^\star ]]></fr:tex>. This is <fr:link href="jms-0189.xml" title="Closure of automaticality under repetition" addr="jms-0189" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-0189" /></fr:link>.</fr:li></fr:ol>

 <fr:p>We are done.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
